ns,\nalbeit with an overall offset of $\\sim 0.06\\%$. The NL-IPC inferred from hot\npixels is too small to explain the cross-correlation measurement, further\nsupporting the BFE hypothesis. This work presents the first evidence for the\nBFE in an H4RG-10 detector, demonstrates some of the useful insights that can\nbe gleaned from flat field statistics, and represents a significant step\ntowards calibration of WFIRST data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Jun 2019 06:43:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Jan 2020 00:02:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-27"}
